# Keep docs/OVERVIEW.md Up to Date

After **every substantive change** to this project, append a new entry to the **Change Log** section at the bottom of `docs/OVERVIEW.md`.

## Required entry format

```markdown
### YYYY-MM-DD — Short title describing what changed

**What was done:**
- Bullet point explaining each change
- Include WHY if not obvious

**How it works:**
- Brief explanation of any new logic or behaviour introduced

**Files affected:** `path/to/file.ext` (new|modified|deleted)
```

## Rules

- Add the entry **above** the `_Add new entries above this line_` footer line
- Most recent entry goes **first** (reverse chronological)
- If you only updated `docs/OVERVIEW.md` itself (e.g. fixing a typo in the docs), you do NOT need a new change log entry
- If a feature or section of OVERVIEW.md is now outdated due to your change, update that section too
- Keep entries concise — 3-10 bullet points max
- Reference `docs/OVERVIEW.md` before making changes to understand the current state of the project
